title_name: Antarctic Krill Oil Omega Boosting Cod Liver Oil Alternative. A Potent Source of EPA, Astaxanthin & DHA for Brain Function, Heart Health, Blood, Hair, Skin, Joints, Connective Tissues & Liver
feature_bullets: When a proper balance of omega-6s to omega-3s is achieved, both your body and mind both reap a number of benefits. Krill oil is a supplement that is rapidly gaining popularity as an alternative to fish oil. It is made from krill, a type of small crustacean consumed by whales, penguins and other sea creatures. It may offer unique benefits such as a smaller dosage, antioxidants, sustainable sourcing and fewer side effects in comparison to regular Fish Oils.,Roughly 20 % of your brain is made up of the essential omega 3 fatty acid DHA which supports the performance of your brain serving as membrane component. You want to support your thinking, your mental energy and your spiritual vitality? Antarctic Krill Oil Omega Boost is your answer.,The fats found in krill oil may be easier for the body to use than those from fish oil, since most omega-3 fats in fish oil are stored in the form of triglycerides. On the other hand, a large portion of the omega-3 fats in krill oil can be found in the form of molecules called phospholipids, which may be easier to absorb into the bloodstream.,Krill oil is used for the same reasons as cod liver oil, flax oil and other omega 3 fatty acids, but is often favoured because it does not cause fishy burps or an after-taste - a common side effect of fish oil. In fact, krill oil may be even more effective at fighting inflammation than other marine omega-3 sources because it appears to be easier for the body to use.,What’s more, krill oil contains a pink-orange pigment called astaxanthin, which may help reduce infammation with antioxidant effects. In fact, a study that found krill oil significantly reduced a marker of inflammation also found that krill oil reduced stiffness, functional impairment and pain in patients with rheumat0id or oste0arthr!tis. It also increased their range of motion.

title_name: Cleanmarine Krill Oil – Packed with EPA & DHA – Omega 3 with Added Astaxanthin and Choline – Vitamin D – Heart, Eye & Brain Health – Joint & Immune Support - 120 Capsules - Multipack

No unpleasant after-taste or reflux common with fish oils

title_name: Ultra Pure Superba Krill Oil 500mg x 240 Capsules (2 Bottles ) - sourced in the unpolluted Waters of the Antarctic. Providing a Rich Supply of Astaxanthin and Omega 3
feature_bullets: THE PUREST KRILL OIL - each capsule provides 500mg of the purest krill oil, sourced directly from unpolluted waters of the northern Antarctic. In these nutrient dense waters, the krill produce an oil that is rich in the beneficial fatty acids and nutrients.,2X TOTAL OMEGA 3 FATTY ACIDS (230mg) - standardised to contain 23% of the beneficial Omega 3 fatty acids, including 124mg EPA and 64mg DHA per daily serving. This is 2x the concentration of most other Krill Oil supplements. WITH MARINE PHOSPHOLIPIDS, ASTAXANTHIN, VITAMIN D, AND CHOLINE - The inclusion of these important compounds in high strength ensures maximum benefit is obtained and sets krill oil apart from other fish oils.,QUALITY TESTED AND ASSURED - To offer an assurance of exceptional quality, we not only sourced the purest krill oil currently available anywhere in the world, but we spent two years finding the right manufacturing partners that held the same ideals as us. All of our supplements are made in multi-million dollar state of the art facilities across the world. Every step of the supply chain is tested and analysed along the way, and before and after product.,RESPONSIBLY SOURCED- Our Superba Krill oil is harvested by Aker Biomarine who are certified under the Marine Steward Council (MSC) program. They work closely with the Commission for the Conservation of Antarctic Marine Living Resources (CCAMLR), and the Norwegian World Wildlife Fund (WWF) and are committed to ensuring a reduced footprint and impact on the environment and sustainable management of marine resources.

feature_bullets: ✔ Antarctic Krill Oil (Euphausia superba) is a natural source of high concentration omega 3 oil, the powerful ANTIOXIDANT astaxanthin, as well as high levels of phospholipids, a fundamental component of human cell membranes. It contains two types of Omega 3 fatty acid: eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA).,✔ Antarctic Krill Oil (Euphausia superba) is a natural source of high concentration omega 3 oil, the powerful ANTIOXIDANT astaxanthin, as well as high levels of phospholipids, a fundamental component of human cell membranes. It contains two types of Omega 3 fatty acid: eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA).,✔ Antarctic Krill Oil (Euphausia superba) is a natural source of high concentration omega 3 oil, the powerful ANTIOXIDANT astaxanthin, as well as high levels of phospholipids, a fundamental component of human cell membranes. It contains two types of Omega 3 fatty acid: eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA).,✔ Krill oil is a supplement that is rapidly gaining popularity as an alternative to fish oil. Krill oil is used for the same reasons as cod liver oil, flax oil and other omega 3 fatty acids, but is often favoured because it does not cause fishy burps or an after-taste, a common side effect of fish oil.,✔ The fact that it contains astaxanthin is also unique. The ultimate antioxidant, researchers have found that it may be more powerful than vitamin E, beta-carotene and lutein. It can also enhance the action of other antioxidants, such as vitamin E and C.,✔ Krill oil is an excellent source of healthy fats. The omega-3 fats in krill oil may be easier to absorb than those in fish oil. EPA and DHA contribute to the normal function of the heart (with a daily intake of 250mg),✔ DHA and EPA contribute to the maintenance of normal blood pressure (with a daily intake of 3g of EPA and DHA) Therefore, it’s a good idea to take a supplement containing EPA and DHA if you don’t consume the recommended eight ounces of seafood per week.
